  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improved safe access for CBE and public school-enrolled girls and boys in Balkh</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In response to the Humanitarian Response Plan (HRP) 2020 revision priorities, Save the Children International (SCI) will implement an integrated package of life-saving and resilience-building interventions in Balkh province, targeting communities in need of both education in emergencies (EiE) support and COVID-19 prevention measures, enabling students and teachers to safely return to school. Given the convergence of needs, SCI will provide a complementary package of EiE and WASH interventions in the targeted districts. In Balkh (five districts), our integrated activities will reach a total of 83,066 beneficiaries directly, including 3,927 adults (40% women and 60% men) and 83,066 children (47% girls and 54% boys). 
Our approach to integration is based on recognition of the potential of different cluster envelopes to provide a holistic, complementary response to COVID-19 in addition to existing priority needs. COVID-19 has exacerbated inequalities in accessing education across the country and created new barriers for engaging with learning during school closure and returning to school safely once classes resume. With funding under EiE, we will provide self-learning materials for vulnerable children who were unable to access distance learning modalities (TV and radio) during the school closure period and thus, fell behind in the curriculum. To enable children and teachers to safely return to community-based education (CBE) classes and hub schools, funding will be used to provide disinfection materials to CBE classes and hub schools, handwashing facilities, soap, clean drinking water tanks, and reusable face coverings for teachers and students in CBE classes. Due to our operational presence in the target districts in Balkh, experience in education in emergencies (EiE) and integrated COVID-19 response, and ability to implement activities in combination to maximize the impact of different envelopes, we are equipped to lead an integrated response and contribute to the objectives of the HRP 2020.</narrative>
  </description>
